I’m honored to have been a panelist for this conversation about mental health management. Over the years, I’ve been candid about my experiences and to have a platform to share them is such a privilege. It was an amazing experience and I met so many driven, talented, and kind creators. On a personal note, this conversation was a great reminder to be compassionate with myself, to take space if I need it, and above all else, to believe in me. 

Thank you to @ipsy for facilitating this discussion, and thank you to the other panelists for sharing their truths as well @savkstevens @onegrloneworld @dr_ondre 🖤

It’s been a minute since I had this much fun cosplaying a character. Fun fact: Link was my first true cosplay. And the Tears of the Kingdom design is too good not to do. I did dress up as Edward Elric for Halloween as a kid but it wasn’t done with a whole lot of intention 😁🖤

This is my Pride post. The kid me in these photos reveals a few things: I was always creating art, I always liked to wear big shirts, and I always loved Spooky things. That’s about it. My queerness isn’t a matter of whether or not you can “see” who I am. 
I could validate and write down all of the moments that have led up to my existence—and it almost feels like I have to. I’ve had such a rollercoaster of a journey just being myself. I’m queer and genderqueer, and that’s just that. I don’t need to disclose the private and intimate reasons why I am who I am. I have spent my entire career creating transformative makeups, and I know it reflects the person that I am as a whole in so many ways. I even have the privilege of being in drag all the time without all the hate that comes with it. 
I am proud of who I am. I have had a moment in my public “identity” where I was shamed into being less out and less proud of that. There’s so much hate and violence circulating the queer community, and that’s the reason queer people are so loud and choose to take up so much space.
I am so thankful to have people in my life who respect, support, and genuinely love the person I am. 

#happypride #pride #enby #genderqueer #queer

He does know how to sit though, and he is housebroken 🥺🖤 one step closer to the animal sanctuary dream.

Aug 2023 to Jan 2024! Happy New Year and for anyone starting their fitness journey now, you got this!! 💪 For the first time in my life, I can do push-ups. I’m lifting heavier than I ever have. I’ve spent the last 5 months working really hard to get stronger and healthier. And more than anything else, it’s affected my mental health in ways I couldn’t imagine. I was truthfully spending a lot of days in bed, drinking, and then getting short bursts of happiness when I’d go out dancing or spending time with the animals. This journey so far has taught me that my physical and mental health work in tandem. I can’t wait to see the difference in 5 more months from now!
